## Why SQL LIKE queries fail at scale

```sql
-- ❌ Current query
SELECT * FROM products WHERE name LIKE '%running shoes%';
-- 5M rows × full scan × no index usable for LIKE '%...%' = 10 seconds
-- Also misses: 'run shoes', 'running shoe', 'jogging shoes' (synonyms)
```

PostgreSQL B-tree indexes don't help with `LIKE '%...%'` (leading wildcard). Full-text search needs an inverted index.

---

## Understand this first: Inverted Index

```text
Your product documents:
  Doc 1: "Red Nike Running Shoes for men"
  Doc 2: "Blue Adidas Running Shoes lightweight"
  Doc 3: "Leather Formal Oxford Shoes"

Inverted index (word → documents):
  'running' → [Doc 1, Doc 2]
  'shoes'   → [Doc 1, Doc 2, Doc 3]
  'nike'    → [Doc 1]
  'leather' → [Doc 3]

Query 'running shoes':
  → Find docs with 'running': {1, 2}
  → Find docs with 'shoes': {1, 2, 3}
  → Intersection: {1, 2} — both words match
  → Score Doc 1 and Doc 2 by relevance (TF/IDF or BM25)
```

This is O(1) lookup — no matter if you have 1M or 100M products.

---

## Step 1: Add Elasticsearch dependency

```xml
<dependency>
  <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
  <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-data-elasticsearch</artifactId>
</dependency>
```

```yaml
spring:
  elasticsearch:
    uris: http://elasticsearch:9200
    username: elastic
    password: ${ELASTIC_PASSWORD}
```

---

## Step 2: Define the index mapping

```java
@Document(indexName = "products")
@Setting(settingPath = "elasticsearch/product-settings.json")
@Data
@Builder
public class ProductDocument {

    @Id
    private String id;

    @Field(type = FieldType.Text, analyzer = "product_analyzer")
    private String name;

    @Field(type = FieldType.Text, analyzer = "product_analyzer")
    private String description;

    @Field(type = FieldType.Keyword)  // exact match, not analyzed
    private String brand;

    @Field(type = FieldType.Keyword)
    private String category;

    @Field(type = FieldType.Double)
    private Double price;

    @Field(type = FieldType.Boolean)
    private Boolean inStock;

    @Field(type = FieldType.Integer)
    private Integer stockCount;

    // For autocomplete
    @Field(type = FieldType.Search_As_You_Type)
    private String nameAutocomplete;
}
```

**Key field types:**
- `FieldType.Text` + analyzer: tokenized, stemmed, analyzed — good for full-text search
- `FieldType.Keyword`: exact match only — good for filters (brand = "Nike"), sorting, aggregations
- `FieldType.Search_As_You_Type`: built-in autocomplete support

---

## Step 3: Custom analyzer configuration

```json
// resources/elasticsearch/product-settings.json
{
  "analysis": {
    "analyzer": {
      "product_analyzer": {
        "type": "custom",
        "tokenizer": "standard",
        "filter": [
          "lowercase",
          "stop",
          "product_synonyms",
          "product_stemmer"
        ]
      }
    },
    "filter": {
      "product_synonyms": {
        "type": "synonym",
        "synonyms": [
          "running, jogging",
          "shoes, sneakers, footwear",
          "pants, trousers"
        ]
      },
      "product_stemmer": {
        "type": "stemmer",
        "language": "english"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

**What the analyzer does to query "Running Shoes":**
```text
1. Tokenize: ["Running", "Shoes"]
2. Lowercase: ["running", "shoes"]
3. Stop words: ["running", "shoes"]  (no change)
4. Synonyms:   ["running", "jogging", "shoes", "sneakers", "footwear"]
5. Stemming:   ["run", "jog", "shoe", "sneaker", "footwear"]

Now matches: "running shoes", "jogging sneakers", "run footwear", etc.
```

---

## Step 4: Search repository and queries

```java
@Component
@RequiredArgsConstructor
public class ProductSearchService {

    private final ElasticsearchOperations esOps;

    public SearchHits<ProductDocument> search(ProductSearchRequest request) {

        BoolQuery.Builder queryBuilder = QueryBuilders.bool();

        // Full-text search on name and description
        // name gets 3x boost — matching in title is more important
        if (StringUtils.hasText(request.getKeyword())) {
            queryBuilder.must(QueryBuilders.multiMatch(mm -> mm
                .query(request.getKeyword())
                .fields("name^3", "description")  // ^3 = 3x boost for name
                .type(TextQueryType.BestFields)
                .fuzziness("AUTO")  // allows 1-2 character typos
            ));
        }

        // Exact filters (Keyword fields)
        if (request.getBrand() != null) {
            queryBuilder.filter(QueryBuilders.term(t -> t.field("brand").value(request.getBrand())));
        }
        if (request.getCategory() != null) {
            queryBuilder.filter(QueryBuilders.term(t -> t.field("category").value(request.getCategory())));
        }
        if (Boolean.TRUE.equals(request.getInStockOnly())) {
            queryBuilder.filter(QueryBuilders.term(t -> t.field("inStock").value(true)));
        }

        // Price range filter
        if (request.getMinPrice() != null || request.getMaxPrice() != null) {
            queryBuilder.filter(QueryBuilders.range(r -> {
                r.field("price");
                if (request.getMinPrice() != null) r.gte(JsonData.of(request.getMinPrice()));
                if (request.getMaxPrice() != null) r.lte(JsonData.of(request.getMaxPrice()));
                return r;
            }));
        }

        NativeQuery query = NativeQuery.builder()
            .withQuery(queryBuilder.build()._toQuery())
            .withPageable(request.getPageable())
            .withSort(Sort.by("_score").descending())
            .build();

        return esOps.search(query, ProductDocument.class);
    }
}
```

