## lockAtMostFor vs lockAtLeastFor — why both matter

```text
lockAtMostFor = "30m":
  If Pod-1 JVM crashes mid-job, the lock auto-releases after 30 minutes.
  Without this: lock is held forever → no instance can run the job next month.

lockAtLeastFor = "5m":
  Even if the job finishes in 30 seconds, hold the lock for 5 minutes.
  Why? If clock skew or network issue causes a second instance to start slightly
  late, it won't pick up the lock and re-run a job that just finished.
```

